<tr>
	<td class="alt1" width="175" align="center" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><b>Wontonn</b>
<span class="smallfont">
	<br />
	Initiate<br />
		
	
	<br />
	Joined: Apr 2002<br />
	Location: Sunnyvale, CA
</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I think the guide or GM had said it clear, that "proximity aggro" is over rule by "melee agro". That means, who ever first damaged the mob, or cast a spell directly on the mob has the right to finish off the mob, unless they wiped, then others can move in.<br />
<br />
In your case, the bard clearly stated that he only aggro the room, but he didn't shoot at the statue directly to land the first direct attack. When the statue is pulled pass the other raid force, their melee/caster landed a direct melee attack on Statue and gian agro. Since they landed the FIRST DIRECT ATTACK on statue, they become the rightful raid force to claim statue.<br />
<br />
That'd been VT's policy for quiet a while. I know it isn't fair, and a lot of raid force isn't very happy about it. But wasting your breath argue with the GM won't get you anywhere.  <img src="images/smilies/frown.gif" border="0" alt="" title="frown" smilieid="2" /><br />
<br />
Edit: Sarlom, Use the example you listed in your post. If their puller didn't land a direct attack on Mob when he pull, and you cast a slow on the mob when it ran pass your camp. You became the first to land a direct attack thus the mob become yours. It is a KS in most of the players' eye. But if they bring the case to Verant they won't do a thing about it.<br />
<br />
If your Tank use AE taunt when the mob run pass you camp, but their Monk turn around and throw a throwing weapon at the mob and landed, Then even if the mob ran into your camp they can call GM and say you KS them.  As long as they have the log to proof their monk landed the first attack. Since as the GM said, "proximity aggro is over rule by melee agro", AE taunt is proximity aggro, and a throwing weapon did damaged the mob is Melee aggro. So they win, you lost if this is the case.</p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br />Wontonn Soupnoodle<br />
65 Prophet in E'ci<br />
Member of Ethereal Realm</div>
	
