	<p>Hiho,<br />
<br />
this is a bad ruling IMHO. The only way to find out if the bard pulling really did have "melee aggro" would be to melee aggro statue yourself.<br />
Now: Even if he got melee aggro you just might outdamage him. This would have been stealing the mob and you would get a warning (and maybe more).<br />
<br />
If you don't apply any "rules" and just go by the stuff that happened, most will agree that this was in fact kill stealing. It's very clear that you cleared the way to Statue and did pull him not by accident but to bring it to your raid force and kill it. Only way to avoid those situations is to talk with the other guild(s) involved and try to prevent such a thing for the next time.<br />
