	<!-- message -->
	<p>First to Actively Engage is pretty much the only rule they even think about considering, in my experience... and with reason.  Mainly this is in effect, I believe, to prevent people from kiting a mob around and claiming that they have exclusive rights to it.  i.e. Lodizal, Gorenaire, etc...<br />
<br />
Now in this particular case, it's damn ****ty of whoever did it to have swiped your pull, since you apparently did have a force in place, but GMs will rarely do anything about that sort of thing after the fact.  IF the GM was there and witnessed what happened, I'd be sorely dissapointed if he didn't force the other guild to back down but that's the breaks and why many guilds petition in advance when racing for a mob.  The downside to that is that they often just force a roll on who gets first shot and any ideas of a fair race is blown since it's all up to chance and the RNG at that point.<br />
<br />
*shrug*</p>
	
	
	
