	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Shadowshot</b><br /><i>Decided to check what the PNP actually says about this:<br />
<br />
"1. You may not steal kills.<br />
<br />
Kill Stealing is defined as the killing of an NPC for any reason that is already fighting or pursuing another player or group that is prepared to engage that same NPC without that group's specific permission.<br />
<br />
I could find no mention of melee-agro vs proxi-agro.  I would say Statue was yours due to the fact that it was agro'd and you were prepared to deal with it.  GM botched that one IMO.<br />
<br />
If someone can find other information, feel free to correct me.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>That's the general idea of KS. However, things get more complicated in real world so Sony had given their GM some specific guide line on how to handle these kind of incident. <br />
<br />
If follow the rule above, what if a monk is FD pulling trying to split up the pull? The mob isn't fighing or pursuing anyone, so it's up for grab?<br />
<br />
Now, I am not trying to say what happened above isn't KS. It looks very much like a KS to me(thou I can't firmly say it, since I'm not there and don't know anything except things posted above). But what I'm trying to do is remind those who don't know, that this is the rule GMs will follow. Better let your puller know about this and remember this when they pull. Do something, some form of damage if possible to scure the pull rather than wasting your breath argue with the GM after the Mob had been KSed by other people.</p>
	
	
	
