	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I view it as a KS, I'm sure most players view it as a KS, and apparently by the last person's post, the rules seem to say it was a KS. But, the GM didn't feel that way, so you got the shaft. But, I don't know about anyone else, I know I always make sure to do some damage to the mob so people know it's taken, and because the aggro will hold more than prox aggro. If you ever spent time in Rathe, you learn why, as in if anyone sees a giant at 100%, it's getting attacked, whether you have it slowed, or rooted, or whatever, unless you do some damage first (and quickly too), it's getting taken from you. Don't make it right, but that's the way it goes at times.</p>
	
	
	
