	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>"What you did was not a pull. They did not steal your pull."<br />
<br />
And in the pnp its stated: "Kill stealing is defined as the killing of an npc that is already fighting or <u>pursuing</u> another player or group that is prepared to engage that same NPC without that group's specific permission."<br />
<br />
So judging by pnp, it was 100% a kill steal, since the statue was pursuing the bard to a prepared raid force.<br />
<br />
Melee agro over proximity agro...that's bull**** imho. Whoever is the first on the actual agro list has the right to kill the mob, if he's prepared to kill it.<br />
<br />
-----<br />
-Jor</p>
	
	
	
	
	
