</span></td>
	
	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>This Stuff about Kill stealing has come up alot for me in the Needlite room, in the echo caverns. I get in to heated talks with other players about "camp stealing" vs "Kill stealing" I have found that many people have a limited understanding about what "Kill stealing" is.  I got in to a fight with a "Drood" who was powerleveling his alt. I had been in the room for about an hour alone, then this "Drood" shows up and has his "alt" attack some of the needlites that where respawing. I thought this was rude, but was okay because there is no such thing as a "camp"  I can't clame the whole room, just clame the Needlilte that I hit first or had chasing me, that one was mine. That worked till the 3d one, I cast slow on the needlite on the far side of the room and it was comming at me, I started to cast my DD spell, and the "Drood's alt" came over and started to melee it, I pointed out that he was now Kill stealing my kill, and he told me to get lost because he was here first and that if i DD he kills again (remember i was casting a DD spell while he attacked so my DD when off just a few sec after the first weapon hit, this was after my slow was on it) any way, He told me he would report me if I did this again because I was the one Kill stealing him.<br />
<br />
After a heated debate it turned in to a free for all trying to fight for the bugs, I gave up because I play the game to let the stress out from work, not make some more for myself after hours.<br />
<br />
I have seen the quote the PNP states about  Kill stealing,  it is a shame that some times spells that make agro are not seen, not all spells that are cast on the creature cause damage, but the creatures don't seem to care they chase/attack you just the same.<br />
<br />
I see it like this, I could be wrong, but if I was in a store shoping, and some one came in and I wanted to fight them for some reason, I could walk up to them and smack them on the head and then the fight would start, or, I could just get close and then cast some nasty saying in their direction about them and they would then come after me and fight me, the end is the same right ?<br />
<br />
(i have been playing since the release, I have not played every day or for weeks at a time, and I have only made it to levle 40 as my high, so remember that I have never seen the end game nor do i pretend to, I just wanted to share a moment that was a kill steal, that I think I would have lost if it went to a GM, by the log that was posted above)</p>
	
	
	
