	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I think this simply boils down to what's verifiable by a GM. A melee attack, casting a spell etc directly on a mob will produce a msg that would be logged and can be verified by a gm going threw the logs. On the other hand pulling another mob in the area to aggro the room or proximity aggroing most likely doesn't produce a msg thats logged and/or not enough information to prove that you aggroed first.<br />
<br />
Yes what the other guild did is pretty crappy but sometimes it simply boils down to what you can prove and with out a direct interaction with the mob in question you can't prove you where the first one to engage.</p>
	
	
	
