	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /> Mainly this is in effect, I believe, to prevent people from kiting a mob around and claiming that they have exclusive rights to it. i.e. Lodizal, Gorenaire, etc...<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Such a situation is already covered in the writen rules :<blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Kill Stealing is defined as the killing of an NPC for any reason that is already fighting or pursuing another player or group that <b>is prepared to engage</b> that same NPC without that group's specific permission.<hr size="1" /></blockquote>Please note that it says "prepared to engage", not "preparing to engage"... so the lone druid kiting Lodi around waiting for his friends to zone in isn't prepared to engage, he is merely preparing and as such has no claim under the rule.</p>
	
	
	
