	<p>Was once told that to be considered 'engaged' with the mob you have had to do actually damage, via spell or weapon, OR have 'attempted' damage, aka swing and miss.  <br />
<br />
There are two sides to this rule.  The obvious downside being the KS that was stated above.  However the 1st damage rule has also worked the other way around when some one has 'pulled' a mob, had it aggro and run, w/o doing damage, but with attempted damage, to have it 'stolen' via proximity/social aggro.  Can go both ways.  <br />
<br />
It's just some people use the PNP to twist it to fit their purpose.</p>
	
	
	
