	<p>okay here is how I see it<br />
obviously the 2 guilds involved had cleared their own side of arena and was both pulling toward statue.<br />
lets say guild A is on left side, Guild B is on right.<br />
<br />
This much we can asume because to me knowlage thats the only place people pull the statue.<br />
<br />
Guild A decides that in order to win the race they will pull all of the statue room including guards and trash mobs. Thus ending the race and giving them the mob yay guild A. Errr no.<br />
<br />
<br />
Let me tell you a little story.<br />
I have seen this rule before and it does exist, same thing happened to me a looong time ago when I was in burning woods at the giant fort, that named poped that drops treeweave, cant actually remember its name off top of my head aint been there in ages.<br />
Well I play a necro at the time lvl 56 pushing close to 60, and there was a druid there maybe around the same level not sure.<br />
<br />
Anyway I go in and see the named at the back of the room in the hut at the back on the right (excuse me if u dont know the zone). Well there is only a few mobs in there so I target the mob next to it and pull with snare, I end up getting the named and 2 anciants and an arbor. Np really i can handle it. So i get them out of the fort first comes the anciant and the arbor while the named and my snared mob is stuck in the wall (they will warp on me soon).<br />
<br />
So i get a snare on the 2 mobs running at me and then wait for the other 2 to pop on me, only the other anciant comes.. hmm strange I thought. so I get them under control and go back and to the right of the fort there is the druid root dotting the Named. BAHHH /petition this drood stole my mob!!<br />
<br />
Back in these days customer service was alot better and so within 10 mins we had a GM in front of us. He came up with the same thing, as far as he was concerned I had go the named as an add, I did no damage to it and so it was assisting the other mob and not as such agro on me. /boggle<br />
<br />
As it happened the druid told me the named only droped an opal and so I didnt care really, and after that me and that same druid became good friends and PLing my new main a few month later <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /><br />
Happy ending, hes now one of my closest friends.<br />
<br />
But the point is the rule is there, and its there for a reason, the reason to stop people pulling tons of mobs in order to grab the one that can drop the ph4t l3wt.<br />
<br />
Not nice how it worked out for guild A, and guild B was not exactly playing Nicely (but not breaking the rule). I think guild A and B should be locked in a room and forced to play nicely. make a statue roter or something <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" />)<br />
<br />
AOW gimp anyhow, my guild just killed RZ, we pwn joo all!!</p>
	
	
	
	
	
